review_blob: Very dark and rich pour with a small head that comes out half as dark as its body. Sweet coffee and chocolate flavors hit you at first followed by subtle vanilla. As the last bit hits the back of your throat you may feel a little tingle from the chili spices. The after taste is much the same as drinking a sweet stout. This beer is different but in a very good way. I highly recommend it to all stout drinkers and for those who dont drink stouts, this might change your mind.
